The following extinct fossil species have been described:

*&quot;Bubalus brevicornis&quot; - 
*&quot;Bubalus cebuensis&quot; (Cebu tamaraw) - 
*&quot;Bubalus fudi&quot; - 
*&quot;Bubalus grovesi&quot; - 
*&quot;Bubalus mephistopheles&quot; (Short-horned water buffalo) - 
*&quot;Bubalus murrensis&quot; (European water buffalo) - 
*&quot;Bubalus palaeokerabau&quot; (Long-horned Javan water buffalo) - 
*&quot;Bubalus platyceros&quot; - 
*&quot;Bubalus teilhardi&quot; - 
*&quot;Bubalus wansijocki&quot; - 
*&quot;Bubalus youngi&quot; - 

